text: Spike is an Australian pay television channel owned by ViacomCBS Networks UK & Australia. Launching on 15 March 2017 on Fetch TV, it is a localised version of the American channel Spike (now Paramount Network), and primarily airs entertainment programming geared towards a male audience, including import dramas, programming from its U.S. counterpart, and mixed martial arts. In July 2016, Spike TV became available to Fetch TV. ==Current Programs== *American Grit *Bellator MMA * Caraoke Showdown * Catch a Contractor * Lip Sync Battle * Naked Attraction * Being Mary Jane * Dog and Beth: On the Hunt * Can't Pay?
